  "prompt": "Could CAT exam and MAT exam take place on same day (4th December 2016)?",
  "response": "The CAT (Common Admission Test) and MAT (Management Aptitude Test) are both entrance exams for management programs in India. Typically, these exams are scheduled on different dates to avoid a conflict for candidates who might wish to attempt both. \n\nOn December 4, 2016, the CAT exam was conducted, and historically, the MAT exam in December is usually scheduled on the first Sunday of the month. However, specific scheduling can vary each year, and it is always determined by the respective organizing bodies. In 2016, it so happened that both exams were indeed scheduled on December 4th. This overlap was unusual since candidates who wanted to attend both had to choose one exam to take because they couldn't be in two places at once. \n\nFor accurate registration and scheduling, candidates are advised to check the official announcements from the organizing bodies.",
